HEADWORD: Seamark
<hw>Sea"mark`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Any elevated object
on land which serves as a guide to mariners; a beacon; a landmark
visible from the sea, as a hill, a tree, a steeple, or the like.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sea mat</ent>⟦br⟧
